om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">SEC Space SPAC</h2><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In November 2019, a s=
pecial purpose acquisition company called Stable Road Acquisition Corp. wen=
t public, raising $172.5=C2=A0million from investors to merge with a compan=
y to be named later. Specifically, according to the first paragraph of <a h=
ref=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/24448786.258945/aHR0cH=
M6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzE3ODExNjIvMDAwMTIxMzkwMDE5M=
DIyNTY1L2Y0MjRiNDExMTlfc3RhYmxlcm9hZGFjcS5odG0/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBdc1=
1ebe5" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #0000=
00; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bott=
om-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">its=
 prospectus</a>, Stable Road was looking =E2=80=9Cto focus our search on co=
mpanies in the cannabis industry which are compliant with all applicable la=
ws and regulations.=E2=80=9D It had 18 months to find one; if it failed, it=
 had to give investors their $150 million back.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px=
 0;">After <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/2444878=
6.258945/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9saXRpZ2F0aW9uL2FkbWluLzIwMjEvMzMtMTA5NT=
UucGRm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB520460f8" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; b=
order-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style:=
 solid; background-color: #ccc;">considering</a> =E2=80=9Cdozens of compani=
es in that industry,=E2=80=9D Stable Road decided not to buy a cannabis com=
pany, and by June 2020 it was casting its net more widely. Specifically in =
outer space. That month, Stable Road=E2=80=99s sponsor Brian Kabot met Mikh=
ail Kokorich, the founder of a company called Momentus Inc., which makes pl=
asma space rockets, or <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/c=
lick/24448786.258945/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9saXRpZ2F0aW9uL2NvbXBsYWludH=
MvMjAyMS9jb21wLXByMjAyMS0xMjQucGRm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB56964f6d" itemp=
rop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-dec=
oration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #0=
00000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">tries=C2=A0to a=
nyway</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Large commercial sat=
ellite launch providers offer launch services to satellite owners but only =
leave these =E2=80=9Crideshare=E2=80=9D satellites in a limited range of or=
bits. Momentus hopes to=C2=A0offer =E2=80=9Clast mile=E2=80=9D satellite pl=
acement services to place these rideshare satellites into custom orbits of =
the customers=E2=80=99 choosing. According to Momentus=E2=80=99s plans, Mom=
entus will integrate its customer=E2=80=99s payload into Momentus=E2=80=99s=
 vehicle, which will then be loaded onto a larger rocket. The rocket will t=
hen leave Momentus=E2=80=99s vehicle in orbit, at which point Momentus will=
 move its vehicle and the customer=E2=80=99s integrated payload into a cust=
om orbit using what it touted in investor presentations as its =E2=80=9Ccor=
nerstone=E2=80=9D technology, a propulsion system using MET water plasma th=
rusters.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Cool! That is not obv=
iously connected to cannabis, but nor is it obviously=C2=A0<em>not=C2=A0</e=
m>connected to cannabis I guess.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway Kok=
orich talked a good game about his plasma space rockets, and Kabot had $172=
.5 million burning a hole in his pocket, so a deal was struck. =E2=80=9CSRA=
C engaged several firms to assist with due diligence, including a space tec=
hnology consulting firm with the expertise to investigate the state of deve=
lopment of Momentus=E2=80=99s technology=E2=80=9D; apparently the space tec=
hnology consulting firm (cool!) declared Momentus=E2=80=99s technology good=
. So Kokorich and Kabot negotiated a merger agreement, and they also pitche=
d other investors on a PIPE (private investment in public equity) to buy an=
other $175 million of Momentus stock alongside the SPAC merger. The deal <a=
 href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/24448786.258945/aHR0=
cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzE3ODExNjIvMDAwMTIxMzkwMDI=
wMDMwNDAzL2VhMTI3ODU0ZXg5OS0xX3N0YWJsZXJvYWQuaHRt/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB=
03153cd8" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
was announced</a> in October 2020.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Yesterda=
y <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/24448786.258945/=
aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9uZXdzL3ByZXNzLXJlbGVhc2UvMjAyMS0xMjQ/607f07ceef4=
b8524a319a23cB703749d4" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" styl=
e=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width:=
 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-=
color: #ccc;">the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission sued</a> Momentus=
, Stable Road, Kokorich and Kabot, claiming that Kokorich was lying to Kabo=
t, and that Kabot passed along those lies to investors. Everyone but Kokori=
ch settled, agreeing to pay a total of $8 million to the SEC, forfeit some =
founders=E2=80=99 shares in the SPAC,=C2=A0and let the PIPE investors get t=
heir money back if they want to.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There are =
two main categories of alleged lies. One is about the plasma space rockets.=
 Specifically, in July 2019 Momentus sent a plasma space rocket up into spa=
ce to test it out, and it basically didn=E2=80=99t work, but Momentus told =
everyone that it did. I=E2=80=99m going to block quote from <a href=3D"http=
s://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/24448786.258945/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc=
2VjLmdvdi9saXRpZ2F0aW9uL2FkbWluLzIwMjEvMzMtMTA5NTUucGRm/607f07ceef4b8524a31=
9a23cC520460f8" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"col=
or: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bo=
rder-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #=
ccc;">the SEC=E2=80=99s order</a> here, not so much because it adds much to=
 the story but because there are a lot of cool space words:</p><blockquote>=
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The El Camino Real mission did not meet any of=
 the public or internal success criteria. After experiencing significant is=
sues with supporting sub-systems and its propulsion system, Momentus achiev=
ed only twelve =E2=80=9Chot firings=E2=80=9D with microwave power turned on=
 out of 23 firings. While a pump issue significantly restricted flow of wat=
er into the thruster during nine of the 12 hot firings, preventing plasma-g=
eneration, data suggests that only three hot firings produced plasma. Howev=
er, none of the firings lasted a full minute and none generated measurable =
thrust. Momentus lost contact with the satellite approximately three months=
 into the planned six-month mission and was never able to attempt the remai=
ning 77 firings it had planned, much less achieve any of the =E2=80=9C100 i=
ndividual burns of 1 minute or more.=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0=
;">The El Camino Real satellite is still in space, but it is not functional=
.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The El Camino Real mission did not demons=
trate the thruster=E2=80=99s ability to provide commercial launch services.=
 The mission yielded no data to suggest that the 2019 version of the thrust=
er would deliver an impulse of any commercial significance, failed to demon=
strate the propulsion system=E2=80=99s reliability of longevity, and did no=
t characterize the performance of the thrusters.</p></blockquote><p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Cool, okay. But Kokorich allegedly lied about the succ=
ess of the mission in an interview in Space News, cool:</p><blockquote><p s=
tyle=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In a September 25, 2019 article in Space News titl=
ed, =E2=80=9CMomentus reports success in testing water plasma propulsion,=
=E2=80=9D Kokorich enthused, after testing had begun on the El Camino Real =
mission, =E2=80=9CWater plasma propulsion is now technologically mature eno=
ugh to be baselined for operational in-space transportation missions.=E2=80=
=9D He also repeated the claim from Momentus=E2=80=99s January 2019 blog po=
st that =E2=80=9Cthe purpose of the El Camino Real mission was to flight de=
monstrate our core propulsion technology so customers, investors and stakeh=
olders can have absolute confidence that Momentus will deliver their payloa=
ds to a given orbit.=E2=80=9D</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=
Some versions of these alleged lies also made it into the slide presentatio=
n that Momentus and Stable Road made to potential PIPE investors, and=C2=A0=
into the original proxy statement/prospectus that Stable Road published aft=
er announcing the merger, the disclosure document that it prepared for SPAC=
 investors to consider whether to approve the deal.[1] <a href=3D"https://l=
ink.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/24448786.258945/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLm=
dvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzE3ODExNjIvMDAwMTIxMzkwMDIwMDM0MzY4L2ZzNDIwM=
jBfc3RhYmxlcm9hZGFjcS5odG0/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB640a7629" itemprop=3D"S=
toryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration:=
 none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; b=
order-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">That document</a>, inci=
dentally, came out in November 2020; there has still been no shareholder vo=
te on the deal, and the most recent revised proxy/prospectus, <a href=3D"ht=
tps://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/24448786.258945/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3c=
uc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzE3ODExNjIvMDAwMTIxMzkwMDIxMDM2NDY0L2=
ZzNDIwMjFhNF9zdGFibGVyb2FkYWNxLmh0bQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB6041d3ed" ite=
mprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-d=
ecoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: =
#000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">dated this Mo=
nday</a>, contains more accurate disclosure about the El Camino Real test s=
atellite.[2]</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The other alleged lies were ab=
out Kokorich=E2=80=99s immigration status and, uh, national-security status=
? Kokorich is Russian <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/cl=
ick/24448786.258945/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9saXRpZ2F0aW9uL2FkbWluLzIwMjE=
vMzMtMTA5NTUucGRm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cD520460f8" itemprop=3D"StoryLink"=
 itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !im=
portant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bot=
tom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">and</a>, =E2=80=9Cbecause Kokori=
ch is a foreign national, he could not access parts of Momentus=E2=80=99s t=
echnology without an export license.=E2=80=9D Momentus applied for that lic=
ense and it was denied, =E2=80=9Cfor reasons related to national security.=
=E2=80=9D Also he was in the U.S. on a work visa, and in 2018 his visa was =
revoked. He applied for asylum and that was also denied. In January 2021 =
=E2=80=94=C2=A0after the merger was signed and announced =E2=80=94=C2=A0he =
stepped down as CEO of Momentus and left the U.S.; he currently lives in=C2=
=A0Switzerland. Momentus is still under a bit of a national-security cloud;=
 Kokorich has agreed to divest all his Momentus shares, and Momentus has ag=
reed =E2=80=9Cto implement increased security measures and appoint a CFIUS-=
approved director to its board of directors,=E2=80=9D so that it can get U.=
S. government approval to launch satellites. But, according to the SEC, =E2=
=80=9CMomentus and Kokorich did not share the extent of Kokorich=E2=80=99s =
national security issues with SRAC and Kabot,=E2=80=9D and the original pro=
xy/prospectus expressed more optimism about Kokorich staying in the U.S. an=
d remaining CEO of Momentus than was justified by the facts.</p><p style=3D=
"margin: 16px 0;">This is as far as I can tell the first SEC securities-fra=
ud case from the current SPAC boom. It won=E2=80=99t be the last. The SEC h=
as made it clear that it has <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness=
.com/click/24448786.258945/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2Fy=
dGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDQtMTIvbWF5YmUtc3BhY3MtYXJlLXJlYWxseS1pcG9z/607f07ceef4b85=
24a319a23cBa44cdd69" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;"> no love for SPACs</a>, and that it is going to=C2=A0<a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/24448786.258945/aHR0cHM6L=
y93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDQtMTMvZ3JhYi1zcGFj=
LW1lZ2EtbWVyZ2VyLWlzbi10LW1lZ2Etd2l0aG91dC1ibGFja3JvY2stcGlwZQ/607f07ceef4b=
8524a319a23cB7e42380d" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;"> enforce=C2=A0the letter of the law against SPACs</a>. There a=
re other companies that have done SPAC mergers=C2=A0and then,=C2=A0uh, <a h=
ref=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/24448786.258945/aHR0cH=
M6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDItMjYvc3RhcnR1c=
HMtc29tZXRpbWVzLXN0cmV0Y2gtdGhlLXRydXRo/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB273881a0" =
itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; tex=
t-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-colo=
r: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> admitted =
to making false statements</a> to investors? Presumably those will be of in=
terest to the SEC?=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But the Momentus c=
ase shows how weird SEC SPAC enforcement is going to be. For instance here =
is a strange little question: Who was harmed by Momentus=E2=80=99s alleged =
lies? Obvious answers might include =E2=80=9CStable Road,=E2=80=9D or =E2=
=80=9CStable Road=E2=80=99s public shareholders,=E2=80=9D or =E2=80=9Cthe P=
IPE investors=E2=80=9D: Momentus allegedly lied about its technology and it=
s CEO=E2=80=99s immigration status, causing Stable Road and the PIPE invest=
ors to agree to overpay for its stock. Fine. But the SEC is going after Sta=
ble Road=E2=80=99s sponsors=C2=A0too, for <em>being lied to</em>, and for n=
ot catching the lies. And reasonably enough. The <a href=3D"https://link.ma=
il.bloombergbusiness.com/click/24448786.258945/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9u=
ZXdzL3ByZXNzLXJlbGVhc2UvMjAyMS0xMjQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cC703749d4" item=
prop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-de=
coration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #=
000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">SEC=E2=80=99s =
press release</a> says:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=
=9CThis case illustrates risks inherent to SPAC transactions, as those who =
stand to earn significant profits from a SPAC merger may conduct inadequate=
 due diligence and mislead investors,=E2=80=9D said SEC Chair Gary Gensler.=
 =E2=80=9CStable Road, a SPAC, and its merger target, Momentus, both misled=
 the investing public. The fact that Momentus lied to Stable Road does not =
absolve Stable Road of its failure to undertake adequate due diligence to p=
rotect shareholders. Today=E2=80=99s actions will prevent the wrongdoers fr=
om benefitting at the expense of investors and help to better align the inc=
entives of parties to a SPAC transaction with those of investors relying on=
 truthful information to make investment decisions.=E2=80=9D</p></blockquot=
e><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you sponsor a SPAC, you are to some exten=
t just a conduit, a service provider connecting public investors who want a=
 company with a company that wants public investors. But you have to provid=
e the service! And that includes doing some due diligence on the company yo=
u=E2=80=99re acquiring, to make sure that it isn=E2=80=99t selling lies to =
your investors.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In any case, though,=C2=A0t=
he lies were eventually discovered =E2=80=94=C2=A0perhaps through the SEC=
=E2=80=99s intervention, perhaps not =E2=80=94=C2=A0and last month the merg=
er agreement was amended to reduce the price. The most recent <a href=3D"ht=
tps://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/24448786.258945/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3c=
uc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzE3ODExNjIvMDAwMTIxMzkwMDIxMDM2NDY0L2=
ZzNDIwMjFhNF9zdGFibGVyb2FkYWNxLmh0bQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cC6041d3ed" ite=
mprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-d=
ecoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: =
#000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">amended proxy=
/prospectus explains</a> (page 30) that the merger agreement was amended on=
 June 29; the amendment, =E2=80=9Camong other things, =E2=80=A6=C2=A0reduce=
d the enterprise value of Momentus from $1.131 billion to $566.6 million.=
=E2=80=9D They cut the price in half to account for Momentus=E2=80=99s vari=
ous troubles. The deal hasn=E2=80=99t closed yet, and the SPAC=E2=80=99s sh=
areholders could still vote it down (or get their money back)=C2=A0if they =
don=E2=80=99t like what they read in the new proxy/prospectus or the SEC or=
der. Momentus allegedly lied about its business to sell stock, but it hasn=
=E2=80=99t actually sold any stock yet. The SEC=E2=80=99s press release say=
s:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9COur enforcement tea=
m worked with incredible speed, efficiency, and creativity to file today=E2=
=80=99s actions so that investors will have the benefit of complete and acc=
urate information when voting on the proposed merger,=E2=80=9D said Melissa=
 R. Hodgman, Acting Director of the SEC=E2=80=99s Division of Enforcement.=
=C2=A0</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So everything=E2=80=99s=
 fine! Now you might object that that=E2=80=99s no defense, there=E2=80=99s=
 no =E2=80=9Cno harm no foul=E2=80=9D defense to securities fraud, and even=
 attempting to sell stock by lies is illegal. But there=E2=80=99s a more im=
portant objection, which is that Momentus may not have sold any stock yet, =
but people sure have=C2=A0<em>bought=C2=A0</em>stock. Because remember that=
, while all of this was going on, Stable Road=E2=80=99s stock traded public=
ly on the stock exchange. It sold stock, at $10 per share, as a blank-check=
 company back in November 2019. And then, as a pool of money hunting for a =
deal, it traded at around $10 per share. When it announced a merger with a =
cool space company, its stock went up. Cool space company! Successfully tes=
ted its plasma rockets in space! CEO probably wasn=E2=80=99t getting deport=
ed! The stock closed as high as $27.42 per share this February.[3] Then muc=
h of that enthusiasm drained away; the stock closed at $11.88 yesterday.[4]=
=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Everyone who bought Stable Road stoc=
k between the announcement of the merger (November 2020) and, let=E2=80=99s=
 say, Monday (the most recent revised proxy/prospectus) has some claim that=
 they were deceived by Momentus=E2=80=99s alleged lies, that they overpaid =
for Stable Road stock because (1) they expected it to transform into Moment=
us stock when the merger closed and (2) they thought Momentus was better th=
an it was. The fact that Momentus and Stable Road=C2=A0<em>corrected=C2=A0<=
/em>those alleged lies before the merger closed, and before Momentus sold a=
ny stock, isn=E2=80=99t good enough: Even before the deal closed, Stable Ro=
ad=E2=80=99s stock traded on the stock exchange, and its price moved based =
on what Momentus=E2=80=99s and Stable Road=E2=80=99s statements=C2=A0about =
Momentus=E2=80=99s business. If those statements were wrong, there are goin=
g to be aggrieved shareholders, even if they are not technically <em>Moment=
us=C2=A0</em>shareholders yet.</p><h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-fami=
ly: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: =
-1px; font-size: 20px; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotte=
d; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px 5px;">Saudi! Arabia! Green! Bond!</h2><p =
style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Saudi=C2=A0Arabia <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bl=
oombergbusiness.com/click/24448786.258945/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYXJnYWFtLmNvbS9lb=
